In the assumption that we are concerned, the players did not act to evade the application of the sanction (this would be a clear case of law fraud), but rather chose when to submit to it.
They made a strategic decision without drawing the punishment or fleeing it.
Although the border between engineering and law fraud is widespread, on this occasion I think it was a clear case of ingenuity.
The controversy, I think, arises by two factors: because it was two self-expulsion and by the way in which the transmission of the directive to provoke them was carried out.
